I strongly object to paying for a game like this and then paying extra just to get hints. They are not necessary as there a youtube videos showing exactly how to solve problems. You also have to pay to be able to move around the game quickly. Again not really necessary as it isn't to slow just to do it the usual way. Part of the game's complexity is simply having to go backwards and forwards all over the place. Not that mentally stimulating, just tedious.  The puzzles themselves don't make any sense of any kind of storyline. You just seem to go around pick up random stuff and do random things. There is no sense of why you need to do things, how solving one problem then leads logically to the next puzzle. To the developers: Do not charge for things that should be included in the package, your business model just puts people (like me) off the brand - I won't look here again. And think of puzzles that make sense in terms of a story, not just random stuff linked by pretty pictures and lots of wandering back and forth!

I loved the other Syntaxity games, as they are so Myst-like, so I was looking forward to this one. Very good puzzles, but I didn't like that you have to pay extra just for hints and for fast-travel, so I didn't buy either. Can't remember this being the case in the older Syntaxity games, where I'm sure I used fast-travel without paying extra for it. The game itself is quite short. It only felt long for me as I didn't use the hints and went back and forth countless of times because I was stuck a few times.
